## The goal of fundamentals of a good developer mindset:

This article discusses issues that programmers run into when trying to modify their code. The program may become more challenging to use and complex as a result of these issues. The article offers advice to programmers on how to create programs that are clearer and simpler to use. The most important piece of advice is to keep in mind that the program's goal is to assist users, not to show off the developer's superior thinking.
It highlights the significance of embracing the basic laws of software and having a mentality that prioritizes creating software that is simple and easy to maintain. I will mention some of the points that article shows, including understanding the purpose of software, designing systems that can be created and maintained easily, fully understanding their work, and prioritizing simplicity.
